<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Rocker Arm Assembly, Camshaft
        Assembly, Tappets, and Push Rods - Assemble
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s210010505">
        <title>Assemble</title>
        <svcproc id="s210010505.1" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Valve Lever (Rocker Arm) Assembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate all valve lever bores with clean engine oil. Install retaining ring at one end
                    of the shaft and assemble components.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010525" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8563B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Assemble valve lever components</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Arrange valve lever assembly components.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The word "TOP" marked on rocker shaft should face up at all times. Shaft support brackets
                            should be assembled so part numbers face down.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f210010526" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8565.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Valve lever assembly arrangement</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining ring (each end of shaft)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Valve lever (12 locations)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Bracket (6 locations)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Spring (5 locations)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker shaft</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Cup plug (each end of shaft)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Brackets must line up over shaft bolt grooves. See for valve lever bracket assembly
                            correct end view position of shaft oil holes to mounting bracket.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010527" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8572.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Correct end view orientation of valve lever bracket assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder head</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Shaft position</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Shaft oil holes</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When all components of shaft have been installed in correct order, attach retaining ring
                    to secure components to shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010528" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8566.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install valve lever shaft retaining ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
